During our stay on Saturday, the entire street in front of the hotel (Hornby) was closed for a city block due to a large crane loading glass into a building across the street.	Make sure you get a room at the front (overlooking Hornby St) as a room to the rear has a terrible view and the noise from the alley below starts at 5:30am.	Unfortunately there was a lot of building work going on, so it was not an attractive or quiet view, but not the hotel's fault.	The executive room is spacious, well lit, and the bathtub for two in the corner of the room is spectacular.